      <hedline>
        <hl1>Priorities for Turkey</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Anne M Rice letter on Sept 15 article on schools in Turkey says government should reconsider its spending priorities</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''As Turkey's Schools Open, a Million Are Left Out'' (Yenidogan Journal, Sept. 15):</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''As Turkey's Schools Open, a Million Are Left Out'' (Yenidogan Journal, Sept. 15):</p>
        <p>The situation of Turkey's poor, especially its children, should be a matter of great concern. According to your article, Turkey is increasing its military spending. The Turkish government should be encouraged to shift its spending priorities instead.</p>
        <p>In July, Turkey announced its intention to buy 145 attack helicopters from the United States for $3.5 billion. Perhaps the United States needs to reconsider its priorities as well, with a long-range view of what it takes to help build stable, healthy countries.</p>
        <p>ANNE M. RICE  Great Falls, Va., Sept. 16, 2000</p>
      </block>
